author: David Kelly
title: Sunnyside exercises Salpointe demon
text:
Sunnyside exercises Salpointe demon - Tucson News Now Member Center: Saturday, September 12 2015 1:31 AM EDT 2015-09-12 05:31:10 GMT (Source: Raycom Media) The schedules were taken from the Arizona Interscholastic Association. Game times and location are subject to change. The schedules were taken from the Arizona Interscholastic Association. Game times and location are subject to change. TUCSON, AZ (Tucson News Now) - 
Sunnyside’s Nick O’Hagin did what Nick O’Hagin does on Friday night at Doherty Stadium in Tucson. 
He ran and passed the Blue Devils to another win. 
The senior rushed for a pair of touchdowns and threw for another as #10 Sunnyside beat Salpointe Catholic 21-16 ending a five-game losing streak to the Lancers that dated back to 2007. 
O’Hagin scored on a three-yard run and found junior receiver Gabe Soto on a 20-yard touchdown pass to give the Blue Devils (4-2) a 14-3 lead at the break. 
After a power outage extended halftime for several extra minutes, the Lancers defense forced a quick three and out. 
Salpointe Catholic’s offense then found some traction, marching 71 yards in eight plays. Trevor Volpe busted a 22-yard run and then scored from nine yards out to make it 14-10 Sunnyside. 
The Blue Devils though were able to answer right back. A big kick return set-up Sunnyside at the Lancers 38. 
O’Hagin hit Ruben Figueroa on a flat route for 16 yards, and then converted a 4th and nine with a ten-yard run. 
He scored on the next play to push Sunnyside’s lead back to a comfortable 11 points. 
The Blue Devils travel to Cienega next Friday night to face a Bobcats team they have never beaten in four meetings. 
Salpointe Catholic (2-4) saw their playoffs hopes all but disappear with a third straight loss. The Lancers travel to winless Buena in Week Seven.
